    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Moggill well. I understand the lifestyle buyer who drives this market, what they look for in a property and how to structure a campaign that reaches a regional and interstate audience as well as local upgraders. Acreage marketing is a specialised discipline, and that expertise is the difference between a strong result and an underwhelming one.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Moggill Ferry connects the suburb to Riverhills and the south-western corridor, and Moggill Road provides the main spine through to Kenmore and beyond. The Moggill State School catchment is a primary value driver for family buyers, and the suburb's bushland reserves and equestrian-friendly blocks attract a buyer profile that is distinct from the rest of Brisbane. Properties with usable cleared land, established improvements such as stables or sheds, and direct river frontage routinely sell above suburb medians when marketed to the right audience.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
